.\" Automatically generated by Pandoc 1.18
.\"
.TH "updateConf" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
updateConf \- update node configuration.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]db.updateConf(<config>,[options])\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
Sdb
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Update node configuration and reload all configurations.
Some configurations require restart to take effect, some are not allowed to be
changed.
.SH PARAMETERS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]configs\f[] ( json object , \f[I]Required\f[] )
.RS 2
.PP
The specific configurations to update.
Including configuration name and value, format: { preferedinstance:\[aq]A\[aq],
diaglevel:3 }
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]options\f[] ( json object )
.RS 2
.PP
Specify location params, such as NodeID, HostName, ServiceName, etc.
.PP
It only takes effect on coordinate nodes.
The global nodes in default.
.RE
.IP "1." 3
Global
.RS 4
.PP
Specify the command\[aq]s location which is local or global.
.IP \[bu] 2
Global:false : run on local
.IP \[bu] 2
Global:true : run on global nodes
.RE
.IP "2." 3
GroupID
.RS 4
.PP
Specify the command\[aq]s location by group ID.
.IP \[bu] 2
GroupID:1000
.IP \[bu] 2
GroupID:[1000, 1001, ...]
.RE
.IP "3." 3
GroupName
.RS 4
.PP
Specify the command\[aq]s location by group name.
.IP \[bu] 2
GroupName:"db1"
.IP \[bu] 2
GroupName:["db1", "db2", ...]
.RE
.IP "4." 3
NodeID
.RS 4
.PP
Specify the command\[aq]s location by node ID.
.IP \[bu] 2
NodeID:1000
.IP \[bu] 2
NodeID:[1000, 1001, ...]
.RE
.IP "5." 3
HostName
.RS 4
.PP
Specify the command\[aq]s location by node name.
.IP \[bu] 2
The param should be used with \[aq]ServiceName\[aq].
.IP \[bu] 2
HostName:"host\-01"
.IP \[bu] 2
HostName:[ "centos\-01", "ubuntu\-02", ...
]
.RE
.IP "6." 3
ServiceName
.RS 4
.PP
Specify the command\[aq]s location by ServiceName.
.IP \[bu] 2
The param should be used with \[aq]HostName\[aq].
.IP \[bu] 2
ServiceName:"11820"
.IP \[bu] 2
ServiceName:[ "11780", "11810", ...
]
.RE
.IP "7." 3
NodeSelect
.RS 4
.PP
Specify the command\[aq]s node select type for a group
.IP \[bu] 2
without the node information.
Value is "all",
.IP \[bu] 2
"master", "any" or "secondary".
.IP \[bu] 2
NodeSelect:"all"
.RE
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[]
.IP \[bu] 2
Both configurations that take effect immediately and require restart will be
written into config file and become permanent.
.IP \[bu] 2
Configurations that require restart or that is not allowed to change will
provide more detailed information through error message return value.
.IP \[bu] 2
If the default value equals the current value of a certain configuration, then
error message will not be reported.
.IP \[bu] 2
If no location parameter is provided, the default value will be {Global:true},
i.e., effective on all nodes.
.IP \[bu] 2
You can use \f[B]Snapshot(SDB_SNAP_CONFIG)\f[] to aquire current configurations
of a specific node.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
No return value, when exception happen, use getLastError() to get the error code
and use getLastErrMsg() to get error message.
For more detial, please reference to Troubleshooting.
.SH HISTORY
.PP
Since v2.9.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP "1." 3
Set configuration \[aq]diaglevel\[aq] on data node 20000.
.nf
\f[C]
//\ connect\ to\ coord
>\ db\ =\ new\ Sdb(\ "localhost",\ 11810\ )
>\ db.updateConf(\ {\ diaglevel:3\ },\ {\ GroupName:"db1",\ ServiceName:"20000"\ }\ )
\f[]
.fi
.RE
.IP "2." 3
Set configuration \[aq]preferedinstance\[aq] and \[aq]diaglevel\[aq] on all
nodes of group db2.
.nf
\f[C]
//\ connect\ to\ coord
>\ db\ =\ new\ Sdb(\ "localhost",\ 11810\ )
>\ db.updateConf(\ {\ preferedinstance:\[aq]A\[aq],\ diaglevel:3\ },\ {\ GroupName:"db2"\ }\ )
\f[]
.fi
.RE
.IP "3." 3
Get more specific informantion on error.
.nf
\f[C]
//\ connect\ to\ coord
>\ db\ =\ new\ Sdb(\ "localhost",\ 11810\ )
//\ set\ configurations,\ get\ error\ message.
>\ db.updateConf(\ {\ transactionon:\[aq]true\[aq]\ },\ {\ ServiceName:"20000"\ }\ )
(nofile):0\ uncaught\ exception:\ \-264
One\ or\ more\ nodes\ did\ not\ complete\ successfully
Takes\ 0.009322s.
//\ get\ detailed\ information\ that\ config\ \[aq]transactionon\[aq]\ requires\ a\ restart.
>\ getLastErrObj()
{
\ \ \ \ "errno":\ \-264,
\ \ \ \ "description":\ "One\ or\ more\ nodes\ did\ not\ complete\ successfully",
\ \ \ \ "detail":\ "",
\ \ \ \ "ErrNodes":\ [
\ \ \ \ {
\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ "NodeName":\ "ubuntu\-zwb:20000",
\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ "GroupName":\ "db1",
\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ "Flag":\ \-322,
\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ "ErrInfo":\ {
\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ "errno":\ \-322,
\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ "description":\ "Some\ configuration\ changes\ didn\[aq]t\ take\ effect",
\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ "detail":\ "Config\ \[aq]transactionon\[aq]\ require(s)\ restart\ to\ take\ effect."
\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ }
\ \ \ \ }
\ \ \ \ ]
}
Takes\ 0.004652s.
\f[]
.fi
.RE
